[[Translation:Main/en/Building road depots]]{{en/Tutorial}}

Here you will learn how to '''build''' (place, position) the '''road depots''' so they align with your roads.
Road depots are places where you build your road's vehicles (busses & trucks) and also they are used by the running vehicles for servicing, so make sure your vehicles can enter and exit from road depots.
__NOTOC__
== How do I place a road depot? ==
# First of all, you must open the Road construction toolbar - click the road build button [[File:en/Roadcnstr.png]] on the [[Main/en/Game interface#The Menu bar|menu bar]] to display the road construction toolbar:<br/>[[File:en/Road constructionnew.png|none|frame|The road construction toolbar]]
# Click on '''buid road vehicle depot''' button or press "'''5'''". A new window with '''depot''' direction selection will open.<br/>[[File:en/New road depot.png|none|frame|Selecting new depot button]]
# '''Select the direction''' you want your road depot to face - this is where the road's vehicles will exit to roads.
# Now you must '''position the road depot next to your roads''', facing the depot exit towards the road. Besides building on flat land you can also [[Main/en/Build on slopes|build on slopes]].<br/>[[File:en/Road depot direction.png|none|thumb|350px|Window for selecting direction of road depot]]
# Once you are happy with the position, click your mouse to '''place the road depot'''. If there are roads adjacent to the depot, additional section road will be placed automatically.<br/>[[File:en/Tutorial bus 4.png|none|thumb|350px|A newly build road depot with automatically connected section road]]

Remember, you can always '''destroy''' your depot with the '''dynamite tool''' [[File:en/Clear title.png]].

